(one sort from another) To winnow; to sift; to pick out; frequently followed by out.
examples: to try out the wild corn from the good

senses.sense: (nautical) To extract oil from blubber or fat; to melt down blubber to obtain oil
To extract wax from a honeycomb
To test, to work out.
To make an experiment. Usually followed by a present participle.
examples: I tried mixing more white paint to get a lighter shade.

senses.sense: To put to test.
examples: I shall try my skills on this.

senses.sense: (specifically) To test someone's patience.
examples: You are trying my patience.
Don't try me.

senses.sense: (figuratively, chiefly used in the imperative) To receive an imminent attack; to take.
To taste, sample, etc.
examples: Oh, you need to try the soup of the day!

senses.sense: To prove by experiment; to apply a test to, for the purpose of determining the quality; to examine; to prove; to test.
examples: to try weights or measures by a standard;  to try a person's opinions

senses.sense: (with indirect interrogative clause) To attempt to determine (by experiment or effort).
examples: I'll try whether I can make it across town on foot.

senses.sense: (legal) To put on trial.
examples: He was tried and executed.

senses.sense: To experiment, to strive.
To have or gain knowledge of by experience.
To work on something with one's best effort and focus.
examples: Dad, for fuck's sake, I'm trying my best!
You are trying too hard.

senses.sense: (obsolete) To do; to fare.
examples: How do you try! (i.e., how do you do?)

senses.sense: To settle; to decide; to determine; specifically, to decide by an appeal to arms.
examples: to try rival claims by a duel;  to try conclusions

senses.sense: (euphemism, of a couple) To attempt to conceive a child.
(nautical) To lie to in heavy weather under just sufficient sail to head into the wind.
To strain; to subject to excessive tests.
examples: The light tries his eyes.
Repeated failures try one's patience.

senses.sense: (slang, chiefly AAVE, used with another verb) To want
examples: I am really not trying to hear you talk about my mama like that.

senses.sense: An attempt.
examples: I gave unicycling a try but I couldn’t do it.

senses.sense: An act of tasting or sampling.
examples: I gave sushi a try but I didn’t like it.

senses.sense: (rugby) A score in rugby league and rugby union, analogous to a touchdown in American football.
examples: Today I scored my first try.
